        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 20 at 10:32PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 1032 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles east of Taylorsville, or 4 miles southwest of Love Valley,
moving northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hiddenite, Harmony, Olin, Sheffield, Vashti, Union Grove, Stony
Point, Love Valley, Taylorsville, and Scotts.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
